Man wants Sh1 Million monthly stipend from father's estate             Joackim Bwana  24th Oct 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joackim Bwana  24th Oct 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joackim Bwana   Jagjit Singh Gurumukh Pandhaal in court where he is seeking sh. 1.1 million monthly stipends for his kids and wife from his late father's multi-billion estate in Mombasa. Jagjit who lives abroad has accused his elder brother Tajinder Singh Pandhal of locking him out of his late father's multi-billion vast state while enjoying all the proceeds of the estate and seeks to have the will revoked. [Joackim Bwana, Standard]    Jagjit Singh Gurumukh Pandhaal in court where he is seeking sh. 1.1 million monthly stipends for his kids and wife from his late father's multi-billion estate in Mombasa. Jagjit who lives abroad has accused his elder brother Tajinder Singh Pandhal of locking him out of his late father's multi-billion vast state while enjoying all the proceeds of the estate and seeks to have the will revoked. [Joackim Bwana, Standard] Jagjit Singh Gurumukh Pandhaal in court where he is seeking sh. 1.1 million monthly stipends for his kids and wife from his late father's multi-billion estate in Mombasa. Jagjit who lives abroad has accused his elder brother Tajinder Singh Pandhal of locking him out of his late father's multi-billion vast state while enjoying all the proceeds of the estate and seeks to have the will revoked. [Joackim Bwana, Standard] Jagjit Singh Gurumukh Pandhaal in court where he is seeking sh. 1.1 million monthly stipends for his kids and wife from his late father's multi-billion estate in Mombasa. Jagjit who lives abroad has accused his elder brother Tajinder Singh Pandhal of locking him out of his late father's multi-billion vast state while enjoying all the proceeds of the estate and seeks to have the will revoked.              SEE ALSO :Mumbi Ngugi ruling spells doom to governors, MPs, MCAs SEE ALSO : Mumbi Ngugi ruling spells doom to governors, MPs, MCAs           Fo